14:24.367 --> 14:28.900
* Remember the memories

14:30.767 --> 14:31.767
(man)
Hi there, friend.

14:31.767 --> 14:33.933
- Wow, Tom Green.
- Who?

14:33.933 --> 14:35.067
You work here?

14:35.067 --> 14:36.433
Oh, I always make
time to teach kids

14:36.433 --> 14:37.967
the facts
about A.D.D.

14:37.967 --> 14:40.600
and/or A.D.H.D.,
its hyperactive cousin.

14:40.600 --> 14:42.633
- Huh?
- Hey, you're reading my book.

14:42.633 --> 14:44.233
Touch the book.

14:44.233 --> 14:47.967
Lick the book. Lick the book.
Lick the book. Lick the book.

14:47.967 --> 14:49.567
Lick the book. Lick the book.

14:49.567 --> 14:51.700
Lick the book. Lick the book.
Lick the book. Lick the book.

14:51.700 --> 14:55.933
Book, book, book, book,
book, book, book, book.

14:55.933 --> 14:57.367
Yeah, I haven't read it either.

14:57.367 --> 14:59.067
People with A.D.D.,
they aren't good readers.

14:59.067 --> 15:00.500
Want to go shave a dog?

15:00.500 --> 15:02.500
My friend has A.D.D.

15:02.500 --> 15:05.633
And everyone at school treats
him like some kind of leper.

15:05.633 --> 15:07.133
Well, that's discrimination.

15:07.133 --> 15:10.233
Hey, do you want to go
take a dump on my parents' bed?

15:10.233 --> 15:13.733
[squawking]
I'm an albatross.

15:13.733 --> 15:15.133
I'm an albatross.

15:15.133 --> 15:19.667
* I'm flap-flap-flapping
my albatross wings *

15:19.667 --> 15:24.367
* Flap-flap-flapping
my albatross wings *

15:24.367 --> 15:25.733
[glass shatters]

15:25.733 --> 15:27.567
Ahh!

15:28.633 --> 15:29.900
Ahh!

15:30.967 --> 15:33.200
Go ahead, I'm here for you.

15:33.200 --> 15:39.200
I, uh--recently broke up
with my girlfriend, Cleo.

15:39.200 --> 15:43.533
Remember, too much emotion makes
Dr. Scudworth uncomfortable.

15:43.533 --> 15:46.933
But she was the first girl
that gave me--

15:46.933 --> 15:49.333
what's that word?

15:49.333 --> 15:50.633
Feelings!

15:50.633 --> 15:51.633
[sobs]

15:51.633 --> 15:52.900
[squeals]

15:52.900 --> 15:54.967
Is that water leaking
out of your face?

15:54.967 --> 15:55.900
[squeaks]

15:57.200 --> 15:59.233
Ahh!

15:59.233 --> 16:00.300
Er, uh--

16:00.300 --> 16:02.667
Ahh!

16:02.667 --> 16:05.233
What is this
touchy-feely bull crap?

16:05.233 --> 16:06.500
Yech!

16:06.500 --> 16:10.100
I don't want to borrow
this sweater no more.

16:10.100 --> 16:17.300
*

16:17.300 --> 16:18.833
God won't stop talking to me.

16:18.833 --> 16:20.133
His power is in the mix!

16:20.133 --> 16:21.500
I haven't slept in 78 hours.

16:21.500 --> 16:22.533
[chuckles]

16:22.533 --> 16:24.967
Oh, my goodness, I'm tired.

16:26.300 --> 16:28.967
Jeez, that guy is,
like, 45.

16:28.967 --> 16:30.633
(Principal Scudworth)
Whee!

16:30.633 --> 16:33.533
It's experimental surgery time.

16:33.533 --> 16:35.267
Go on, man, do it.

16:35.267 --> 16:36.400
I want you to.

16:36.400 --> 16:38.667
Stick it in my head.
I hope it kills me.

16:38.667 --> 16:41.067
If you're not terrified,
where's the sport?

16:41.067 --> 16:42.333
I don't want to live
in a world

16:42.333 --> 16:44.733
where buds diss their homeboys.

16:44.733 --> 16:46.200
You're a high school principal.

16:46.200 --> 16:47.867
You don't know
what it's like to be lonely.

16:47.867 --> 16:50.867
On the contrary, Gandhi,
some principals

16:50.867 --> 16:52.767
do feel loneliness.

16:52.767 --> 16:56.067
We're not the invincible gods
that teen magazines would

16:56.067 --> 16:58.667
have you believe.

16:58.667 --> 17:02.100
Then I guess there's no hope
for guys like us.

17:02.100 --> 17:03.933
There's always hope, Gandhi.

17:03.933 --> 17:07.067
When life gives you lemons,
you clone those lemons

17:07.067 --> 17:08.800
and make super lemons.

17:08.800 --> 17:10.667
So go down
to that awareness fair,

17:10.667 --> 17:14.867
stand up for what's right,
and bring me back a funnel cake.

17:14.867 --> 17:16.667
But there's no way
out of this place.

17:16.667 --> 17:19.267
Isn't there?

17:20.433 --> 17:24.767
Oh, I think I know
what you're saying.

17:24.767 --> 17:26.867
- [grunts]
[glass shatters]

17:26.867 --> 17:28.167
And turn.

17:28.167 --> 17:30.600
(Butlertron)
You really helped that boy.

17:30.600 --> 17:34.633
I did,
and without the sweater vest.

17:34.633 --> 17:37.700
I guess it wasn't
magic after all.

17:37.700 --> 17:39.933
Or was it?

17:41.900 --> 17:43.067
[crowd gasps]

17:43.067 --> 17:44.567
Is there a Heather in the crowd?
Heather?

17:44.567 --> 17:46.733
Heather, I have
a message for you:

17:46.733 --> 17:48.067
Jerome wants
you to forgive him

17:48.067 --> 17:49.467
for hooking up
with Lupe at Trey's party,

17:49.467 --> 17:52.600
and God is commanding all of us
to give a shout out

17:52.600 --> 17:55.300
to all the locals
at the In-N-Out in La Puente

17:55.300 --> 17:57.233
His power is in the mix!

18:00.733 --> 18:02.133
(radio announcer)
We're 107 FM,

18:02.133 --> 18:06.433
where the mix of fresh
Christian jams slam first.

18:06.433 --> 18:09.067
His power is in the mix.

18:09.067 --> 18:11.200
Coming up, we've got
a rock crusade--

18:11.200 --> 18:13.967
40 minutes of nonstop Amy Grant!

18:13.967 --> 18:18.067
I can't--you know,
I gotta take--okay...

18:18.067 --> 18:20.133
[scoffs]
I can't believe it, eh?

18:20.133 --> 18:23.133
Jerome hooked up with Lupe?

18:23.133 --> 18:24.233
[crowd screams]

18:24.233 --> 18:25.800
What the hell are
you doing here?

18:25.800 --> 18:28.500
You're selling kisses?
I'm buying.

18:28.500 --> 18:31.600
Abe, will you form a mob
and get rid of this loser?

18:31.600 --> 18:35.967
No, but I will inform a mob
with the help of this winner.

18:35.967 --> 18:37.767
- Tom?
- Hi, everybody.

18:37.767 --> 18:39.333
I'm Ottawa's Tom Green.

18:39.333 --> 18:40.367
I live in Hollywood.

18:40.367 --> 18:41.967
[applause]
- Thank you.

18:41.967 --> 18:45.100
So some of you may have
been mean to a kid with A.D.D.

18:45.100 --> 18:46.533
That's not cool.

18:46.533 --> 18:47.533
Coffee?

18:47.533 --> 18:49.333
Anyone--coffee, anyone?

18:49.333 --> 18:50.667
Huh?
Sorry.

18:50.667 --> 18:52.533
I like cotton candy.
Check out my muscle.

18:52.533 --> 18:54.067
Potato chips.
It's a Ferris wheel.

18:54.067 --> 18:56.067
So I guess what I'm trying
to say is--

18:56.067 --> 18:58.767
Plastic bag. Plastic bag.
Plastic bag. Plastic bag.

18:58.767 --> 19:00.633
Plastic bag.
Plastic bag.

19:00.633 --> 19:03.900
Like Mr. Green
so eloquently said,

19:03.900 --> 19:06.967
A.D.D. is not infectious.

19:06.967 --> 19:09.800
What is infectious is ignorance.

19:09.800 --> 19:11.433
If everyone keeps
treating Gandhi

19:11.433 --> 19:12.900
like a contagious freak,

19:12.900 --> 19:15.900
then this isn't
an awareness fair.

19:15.900 --> 19:18.933
It's an awareness unfair.

19:18.933 --> 19:20.533
(man)
Do you think
I was born yesterday?

19:20.533 --> 19:21.633
[crowd murmuring]

19:21.633 --> 19:22.867
(Tom Green)
Who likes cheese?

19:23.933 --> 19:24.967
Abe?

19:24.967 --> 19:27.367
You know what you have to do.

19:27.367 --> 19:28.700
You're right.

19:28.700 --> 19:32.300
(man)
* Am I on time?

19:32.300 --> 19:35.700
* Have I got soul?

19:35.700 --> 19:40.800
* Arrest myself
for being cold *

19:42.167 --> 19:43.167
[grunts]

19:43.167 --> 19:44.800
Dude, that was not cool.

19:44.800 --> 19:46.133
Not cool!

19:46.133 --> 19:50.067
And because of that,
I'm only paying you $4.

19:50.067 --> 19:52.333
My discomfort
with a man kissing another man

19:52.333 --> 19:54.667
is stronger than my hatred
for people with A.D.D.

19:54.667 --> 19:57.867
Hey, let's all accept Gandhi
and shun Abe instead.

19:57.867 --> 19:59.467
[cheering]

19:59.467 --> 20:01.967
Wow, Abe, your brave
homoerotic gesture

20:01.967 --> 20:04.333
has changed
my view about A.D.D.

20:04.333 --> 20:05.633
Just don't touch me.

20:05.633 --> 20:08.667
Gandhi, get on up here
and dance.

20:08.667 --> 20:10.333
But I didn't bring
my dance skins.

20:10.333 --> 20:11.500
Gandhi!

20:11.500 --> 20:13.667
Okay, you got me.

20:15.433 --> 20:16.767
Maybe I can help.

20:16.767 --> 20:19.633
I think God left
one last song in me.

20:19.633 --> 20:21.300
(man)
Ya'll ready for God?

20:21.300 --> 20:24.300
[dance music playing]

20:24.300 --> 20:32.233
*

